# Character Abilities
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Brew Potion|TYPE:ITEMCREATION.WIZARD|DESC:You can create a potion of any 3rd-level or lower spell that you know and that targets one or more creatures.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Spell Focus|APPLIEDTO:Transmutation|TYPE:GENERAL.EPICWIZARD.COSMICDESCRYER|DESC:Add +1 to the Difficulty Class for all saving throws against spells from the school of magic you select.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Greater Spell Focus|APPLIEDTO:Transmutation|TYPE:GENERAL|DESC:Add +1 to the Difficulty Class for all saving throws against spells from the school of magic you select. This bonus stacks with the bonus from Spell Focus.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Improved Familiar|TYPE:GENERAL|DESC:This feat allows spellcasters to acquire a new familiar from a nonstandard list, but only when they could normally acquire a new familiar.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Silent Spell|TYPE:METAMAGIC.WIZARD|DESC:A silent spell can be cast with no verbal components. Spells without verbal components are not affected. A silent spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell's actual level.
